<$fill $name="body">

!! Using the editor preview

# Open any tiddler for editing
# Click the ''eye icon'' (👁) in the editor toolbar
# Select ''snapshots'' from the dropdown — this replaces the preview pane
# The snapshot toolbar appears with:
#* ''Snapshot draft'' button + optional label input
#* ''Compare [Draft|Saved] with:'' toggle + snapshot dropdown
# Take a snapshot, make some changes, then select the snapshot to see diffs

!! Taking a snapshot with a label

Enter a descriptive label before clicking "Snapshot draft":

```
Label: "before refactoring tags"  →  Click [Snapshot draft]
```

If no label is provided, a timestamp-based label is generated automatically.

!! Comparing Draft vs Saved

The toggle switches what the snapshot is compared against:

* ''Draft'' (default): Compares the snapshot against your current unsaved edits
* ''Saved'': Compares the snapshot against the last saved version of the tiddler

!! Rolling back a single field

When viewing a diff, each changed field has an undo button (↩). Clicking it:

* If the field exists in the snapshot: restores that field's value on the draft
* If the field does ''not'' exist in the snapshot: removes the field from the draft

!! Rolling back all fields

The ''Rollback all'' button replaces the entire draft with the snapshot's fields. Fields that were added after the snapshot was taken are removed.

!! Using the action widget in custom UI

```
<!-- Take a manual snapshot -->
<$button>
  Snapshot current version
  <$action-minver op="snapshot" title="My Tiddler" label="before cleanup"/>
</$button>

<!-- Rollback to a specific snapshot -->
<$button>
  Restore backup
  <$action-minver op="rollback" title="My Tiddler" snapshot-id="abc-123" draft=<<draftTitle>>/>
</$button>
```

!! Exporting and importing snapshots

# Open the [[Snapshot Manager|$:/plugins/rimir/minver/manager]]
# Click ''Export all Snapshots'' — creates `$:/minver/export`
# Either:
#* ''Drag'' the export widget into another wiki's browser tab
#* ''Download'' as `minver-snapshots.json` and import manually
# In the target wiki, click ''Import Snapshots'' to load them

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="tip">
<$fill $name="body">
The export includes both auto and manual snapshots from all tiddlers in localStorage.
</$fill>
</$transclude>

!! Recording a change-group

Use the `cg-start` and `cg-stop` operations to record a session of changes:

```
<!-- Start recording -->
<$button>
  Start recording
  <$action-minver op="cg-start" label="refactoring session"/>
</$button>

<!-- Stop recording -->
<$button>
  Stop recording
  <$action-minver op="cg-stop"/>
</$button>
```

While recording is active, all tiddler creates, edits, and deletes are tracked automatically. The record/stop buttons in the page toolbar provide the same functionality.

!! Cross-plugin API example

Other plugins can start and stop recording via TW message dispatch:

```
<!-- Start recording from another plugin -->
<$button>
  Record changes
  <$action-sendmessage $message="tm-minver-cg-start" $param="my-plugin session"/>
</$button>

<!-- Stop recording from another plugin -->
<$button>
  Done
  <$action-sendmessage $message="tm-minver-cg-stop"/>
</$button>
```

This allows any plugin or automation to trigger change-group recording without a direct dependency on minver's action widget.

</$fill>
</$transclude>
