<$fill $name="body">

!! Q: My snapshots disappear after closing the browser. Why?

By default, auto-snapshots are stored only in the wiki's temp tiddlers (session-only). Enable "Persist auto-snapshots to localStorage" in Settings to keep them across sessions. Manual snapshots are always persisted to localStorage.

!! Q: How much localStorage space do snapshots use?

Snapshots are compressed using the native `CompressionStream` API (deflate + base64). Typical compression ratios are 60-80% for text content. Monitor usage via the settings page, which shows current localStorage consumption. Most browsers limit localStorage to 5-10 MB per origin.

!! Q: Can I transfer snapshots between wikis?

Yes. Use the Export button in the Snapshot Manager to serialize all snapshots into a `$:/minver/export` tiddler as JSON. Drag this tiddler (or download and import the JSON) into another wiki, then use the Import button to load the snapshots into localStorage and the wiki store.

</$fill>
</$transclude>
