<$fill $name="body">

!! What it does

minver keeps snapshot versions of your tiddlers directly in the browser. Snapshots are stored compressed in localStorage, hydrated into `$:/temp/minver/*` on wiki load, and integrated as an editor preview type with per-field diffs and rollback.

!! Features

* ''Manual snapshots'' — take a snapshot anytime from the editor preview pane
* ''Auto-snapshots'' — automatically captures the previous version on every save
* ''Auto-snapshots on create/delete'' — captures initial state on creation ("created-*") and final state on deletion ("deleted-*")
* ''Per-field diff view'' — side-by-side comparison with `<$diff-text>`, integrated as editor preview type
* ''Field-level rollback'' — revert individual fields or the entire tiddler to a snapshot
* ''Manager revert'' — revert any snapshot directly from the manager without entering edit mode
* ''Change-groups'' — record a session of changes (creates, edits, deletes) and review/rollback them as a unit
* ''Compressed storage'' — uses native `CompressionStream` API to minimize localStorage usage
* ''Export/Import'' — transfer snapshots between wikis via drag-and-drop or JSON download
* ''Snapshot Manager'' — browse, diff, and clean up all snapshots across the wiki

!! Prerequisites

* TiddlyWiki 5.3.0+
* Theme plugin (`$:/plugins/rimir/theme`) for `rr-` utility classes
* A modern browser with CompressionStream support (Chrome 80+, Firefox 113+, Safari 16.4+)

!! Quick start

# Open any tiddler for editing
# Click the eye icon in the editor toolbar and select ''snapshots''
# Click ''Snapshot draft'' to capture the current draft state
# Edit the tiddler, then select your snapshot from the dropdown to see per-field diffs
# Use the undo button next to any changed field to revert it

!! Change-groups

Change-groups let you record a session of tiddler changes and review or rollback them as a unit.

# Click the record button in the page toolbar to start recording
# Create, edit, and delete tiddlers as needed
# Click stop to finish — the group is persisted to localStorage
# View groups in the "groups" plugin tab: see every operation (create/modify/delete) with before/after states
# Use "Rollback" to undo all changes in the group at once

During recording, operations on the same tiddler are ''coalesced'': multiple edits merge into a single modify, a create followed by edits stays a single create, and a create followed by a delete removes the operation entirely. This keeps groups compact and rollback predictable.

<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template/templates/callout" type="info">
<$fill $name="body">
All data lives in the browser — no server interaction required. minver is entirely browser-side.
</$fill>
</$transclude>

</$fill>
</$transclude>
