<$fill $name="body">

!! Action widget: `<$action-minver>`

|!Attribute |!Description |
|`op` |Operation (see table below) |
|`title` |Original tiddler title (not the draft title) |
|`label` |Snapshot label (for `snapshot` op, optional — defaults to timestamp). Change-group label (for `cg-start`). |
|`draft` |Draft tiddler title (for `snapshot`, `rollback`, `rollback-field`) |
|`source` |`"draft"` or `"saved"` — which version to snapshot (default: `"draft"`) |
|`snapshot-id` |UUID of the target snapshot (for `delete`, `rollback`, `rollback-field`, `revert`) |
|`field` |Field name (for `rollback-field` only) |
|`group-id` |Change-group identifier (for `cg-delete`, `cg-load`, `cg-rollback`) |

!! Operations

|!Op |!Description |
|`snapshot` |Capture current fields as a manual snapshot. Always saved to both wiki store and localStorage. |
|`delete` |Delete a single snapshot by ID. |
|`delete-all` |Delete all snapshots for a tiddler. |
|`rollback` |Replace all draft fields with snapshot fields. Fields not in the snapshot are removed. |
|`rollback-field` |Restore a single field from the snapshot. If the field doesn't exist in the snapshot, it is removed from the draft. |
|`revert` |Apply snapshot fields directly to the saved tiddler (not a draft). Used by the manager to restore a snapshot without entering edit mode. Attrs: `snapshot-id`, `title`. |
|`export` |Serialize all snapshots from localStorage into `$:/minver/export` as JSON. |
|`import` |Load snapshots from `$:/minver/export` into localStorage and wiki store. |
|`clean-all` |Delete all snapshots from both localStorage and wiki store. |
|`cg-start` |Start change-group recording. Attr: `label` (optional description). |
|`cg-stop` |Stop recording, persist the change-group to localStorage. |
|`cg-delete` |Delete a change-group. Attr: `group-id`. |
|`cg-delete-all` |Delete all change-groups from localStorage. |
|`cg-load` |Load group data from localStorage into a temp tiddler for display. Attr: `group-id`. |
|`cg-rollback` |Rollback all changes in a group and delete the group. Attr: `group-id`. |

!! Snapshot object format

```json
{
  "id": "uuid-v4",
  "timestamp": 1710000000000,
  "label": "snapshot-20260310..." | "my custom label",
  "type": "manual" | "auto",
  "fields": {
    "title": "My Tiddler",
    "text": "...",
    "tags": "tag1 tag2",
    "created": "20260310...",
    "modified": "20260310...",
    "custom-field": "value"
  }
}
```

All tiddler fields are captured as strings. Dates are stringified via `$tw.utils.stringifyDate()`, arrays via `$tw.utils.stringifyList()`. Draft-specific fields (`draft.of`, `draft.title`) are stripped — the original title is stored.

!! Temp tiddler layout

|!Tiddler |!Content |
|`$:/temp/minver/snapshots/<title>` |JSON array of snapshot objects for `<title>` |
|`$:/temp/minver/status` |`"loading"` or `"ready"` — hydration state |
|`$:/temp/minver/storage-usage` |Human-readable localStorage usage (e.g., "12.5 KB") |

!! Configuration tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Description |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/max-manual` |`3` |Max manual snapshots per tiddler |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/max-auto` |`3` |Max auto snapshots per tiddler |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/scope-filter` |`[all[]]` |Filter for which tiddlers get auto-snapshots |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/auto-to-storage` |`no` |Persist auto-snapshots to localStorage |

!! localStorage key format

Keys are prefixed with `minver:` followed by the tiddler title:

```
minver:My Tiddler → base64(deflate(JSON.stringify(snapshots)))
minver:$:/my-system-tiddler → base64(deflate(JSON.stringify(snapshots)))
```

!! Export/Import format

The export tiddler `$:/minver/export` contains a JSON object keyed by tiddler title:

```json
{
  "My Tiddler": [ { snapshot }, { snapshot }, ... ],
  "$:/system-tiddler": [ ... ]
}
```

Both auto and manual snapshots are included. Import merges with (overwrites) existing snapshots.

!! Change-group object format

```json
{
  "id": "uuid",
  "label": "string",
  "startTime": 1234567890,
  "endTime": 1234567890,
  "operations": [
    { "id": "uuid", "timestamp": 1234567890, "type": "create|modify|delete", "title": "...", "before": {...}|null, "after": {...}|null }
  ]
}
```

Each operation records the tiddler state before and after the change. `before` is `null` for creates, `after` is `null` for deletes.

!! Change-group temp tiddlers

|!Tiddler |!Content |
|`$:/temp/minver/cg-recording` |Text = group ID when recording, absent when not |
|`$:/temp/minver/change-groups` |JSON index of all groups |
|`$:/temp/minver/cg-active-group` |JSON of in-progress group (live updates during recording) |
|`$:/temp/minver/cg-group/<id>` |Loaded group data for display (populated by `cg-load`) |

!! Change-group configuration

|!Tiddler |!Default |!Description |
|`$:/config/rimir/minver/max-groups` |`10` |Maximum number of change-groups stored in localStorage |

!! Change-group localStorage keys

|!Key |!Content |
|`minver-cg:<group-id>` |Compressed JSON of a single change-group |
|`minver-cg-index` |Compressed JSON array of group summaries |

!! Cross-plugin API (message events)

Other plugins can start and stop change-group recording by dispatching TW messages:

|!Message |!Parameter |!Description |
|`tm-minver-cg-start` |`param`: label (optional) |Start recording a new change-group |
|`tm-minver-cg-stop` |— |Stop recording the current change-group |

</$fill>
</$transclude>
